        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I gathered notes from discussions into https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39454 , and the good news is,\r\n\r\n- we are unblocked to replace even `Range4`/`Range6` with `vim.range`\r\n- metatables have negligible perf impact (as you confirmed); we just need to ensure that our integer indices match the shape of `Range4`/`Range6`",
